# VS Code is pointed at this directory via --user-data-dir (see ../default.nix),
# so it writes its entire runtime profile here. Only User/settings.json and
# User/keybindings.json are tracked; ignore the runtime state VS Code generates.
# This is a best-effort denylist — fine if it misses the occasional new file.

# Caches
Cache/
CachedData/
CachedConfigurations/
CachedProfilesData/
Code Cache/
GPUCache/
DawnGraphiteCache/
DawnWebGPUCache/

# Logs / crash / telemetry
logs/
# *.log
Crashpad/
# crashDumps/

# Per-profile / per-workspace state
User/globalStorage/
User/workspaceStorage/
# User/History/
# User/sync/
# User/profiles/

# Backups and machine-local bits
# Backups/
machineid
languagepacks.json

# Chromium/Electron storage
Local Storage/
Session Storage/
Shared Dictionary/
Service Worker/
# Network/
Dictionaries/
# Cookies
# Cookies-journal
TransportSecurity
Preferences
# QuotaManager
# QuotaManager-journal

# Unsorted
DIPS
DIPS-wal
Local State
SharedStorage
SharedStorage-wal
Trust Tokens
Trust Tokens-journal
code.lock
Network Persistent State
WebStorage/
User/chatLanguageModels.json
